The paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms for swarm robotics, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes and evaluates generic behaviour similarity measures, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The use of sensors and effectors to characterize group-level behaviour suggests a focus on control systems and cybernetics (cs.SY). The evaluation of the proposed measures in tasks such as aggregation and resource sharing suggests a focus on multi-agent systems and distributed algorithms (cs.MA). Finally, the comparison of the proposed measures to task-specific measures involves statistical analysis and machine learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
